This paper discusses a modification of autoencoder networks to turn them into generative models, which is a common topic in machine learning and deep learning. The paper specifically focuses on the use of adversarial networks and introduces a new source of randomness to prevent degenerate solutions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of maximum mean discrepancy (MMD) networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization problem and the performance of the proposed architecture, which could also fall under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
